headline_main: On Politics With Lisa Lerer: After Mississippi

abstract: Dozens of possible 2020 Democratic candidates are mulling, weighing, considering, wondering. Here is a guide to how they are communicating a desire to run without announcing it outright.
snippet: Dozens of possible 2020 Democratic candidates are mulling, weighing, considering, wondering. Here is a guide to how they are communicating a desire to run without announcing it outright.
lead_paragraph: The would-be 2020 Democratic contenders could not be clearer: They are not running for president.

abstract: With Trump using immigration simply for political gain, Democrats need to be the adults and offer a realistic, comprehensive approach.
snippet: With Trump using immigration simply for political gain, Democrats need to be the adults and offer a realistic, comprehensive approach.
lead_paragraph: LIMA, Peru — Kamala Harris, the Democratic senator from California, recently raised eyebrows when she asked Ronald Vitiello, President Trump’s nominee to lead Immigration and Customs Enforcement, whether he appreciated the “perception” that ICE spreads “fear and intimidation” among immigrants the way the Ku Klux Klan did among blacks.

abstract: The Minnesota senator emerged unscathed from the Kavanaugh hearings, then coasted to a third term. Now she is weighing whether her home state appeal can translate nationally.
snippet: The Minnesota senator emerged unscathed from the Kavanaugh hearings, then coasted to a third term. Now she is weighing whether her home state appeal can translate nationally.
lead_paragraph: NORTHFIELD, Minn. — The speculation began the moment Senator Amy Klobuchar walked into the room.

abstract: With the holiday on the heels of the contentious midterm elections, it may be inevitable that your angry uncle or radical niece will turn talk to the campaigns, the migrant caravan or George Soros.
